A self-supported 63Cu target with thickness of about
80 ug/cm2 for measurements at above-barrier energies,
and another thicker self-supported 63Cu target with
the thickness of 140 ug/cm2 for measurements at near-
and below-barrier energies.
Two Si(Au) detectors were placed at +-10
degree to monitor the current quality.
Data were presented by the first author

A detector array including 7 Si(Au)
surface-barrier detectors with an interval of 10
degree for measurements at above-barrier energies
was mounted on a rotatable arm in the reaction chamber
to detect scattering particles.
8 silicon-PIN detectors were fixed with an angle
coverage from 20 to 68 degree and with an interval of
7 degree for measurements at near- and below-barrier
energies, to measure the elastic scattering.

x4freetext: The Q3D magnetic spectrometer coupled with a
multilayer position-sensitive focal plane gas
detector was employed to select and detect the exited
transfer products at above-barrier energies.
In order to detect the transfer
products in the near- and below-barrier energie range,
two silicon telescopes were fixed at the backward
angle region in the chamber, with angle coverage of
99-127 and 144-171 degree, respectively. Each
telescope contained two layers of silicon detectors,
a 20 um single-side strip detector (16 channels),
and a 60 um double-side strip detector (16 X 16 pixels)
Only the statistic errors are considered for
the transfer-reaction cross sections.
